pmg-mobile-quarantine-ui (0.5.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  * spam quarantine: allow marking mails as seen or unseen, so users of a
    shared mailbox can track which mails were already handled without deleting
    them.

  * spam quarantine: load external images of a mail only on demand, through a
    'Load images' control that is shown only when the opened mail references
    external images, to avoid signaling to the sender that a mail was opened.

  * spam quarantine: show the summed positive and negative spam test scores
    next to the net score, to better judge borderline mails where strong
    negative tests can mask many positive hits.

  * spam quarantine: refresh the mail list after an action taken from the mail
    view, so its state stays in sync without a manual reload.

  * spam list: add an 'About' entry to the menu that explains the quarantine
    interface to end users.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Mon, 08 Jun 2026 13:09:11 +0200

